msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Ledger of accounts of Carlo di Bernardo de' Medici and Francesco di Stefano di Risaliti, a Florentine businessman involved in the textile trade, for the years 1573-1576. Often includes the nature of a given transaction and its amount, as well as listing the names of the individuals that act as counterparts in the transaction.

support.watermark: Similar to Briquet, Armoires Lion 1883 (Florence, 1529), but with the lion's snout more defined.

supportDesc.extent: 240 leaves : 328 x 228 mm. bound to 337 x 231 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (paper) + 240 leaves + i (paper); versos numbered [1-240], modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto; irregular contemporary foliation and pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 2 columns with vertical bounding lines in lead; the large column on the left with a brief description of the transaction and the individual who acts as counterpart in the transaction; the smaller one on the right with the amount of the asset or liability in Arabic numerals.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script, perhaps by multiple hands.

binding.p: Contemporary vellum, no. 39 on spine; the heading Entrata e uscita a/2, no. 48, letter A with decorative penwork and signet C F on upper cover; lower cover wraps around upper cover with leather strap; decorative leatherwork on spine.
